# * --title option

# ** 1. --title overrides a report's default title (none, in this case).
<
2024/1/1
  (a)  1
2024/2/1
  (a)  1

$ hledger -f- balance '--title=My monthly view'
My monthly view

                   2  a
--------------------
                   2  

# ** 2. With an empty argument, it suppresses the title
$ hledger -f- bs --title=
             || 2024-02-01 
=============++============
 Assets      ||            
-------------++------------
-------------++------------
             ||          0 
=============++============
 Liabilities ||            
-------------++------------
-------------++------------
             ||          0 
=============++============
 Net:        ||          0 

# ** 3. --title also affects csv or tsv output.
$ hledger -f- balancesheet --quarterly --title=Hi -O csv
"Hi",""
"Account","2024-03-31"
"Assets",""
"Total:","0"
"Liabilities",""
"Total:","0"
"Net:","0"

# ** 4. And with a null argument, suppresses the title row.
$ hledger -f- balancesheet --quarterly --title= -O csv
"Account","2024-03-31"
"Assets",""
"Total:","0"
"Liabilities",""
"Total:","0"
"Net:","0"

